The plugin lj-widget implements a WordPress widget that displays your LiveJournal
name and links to your account in the sidebar. It uses the LiveJournal FOAF
(Friend of a Friend) interface. 

Copyright 2015 by Gary McGath; available as open source under the MIT License.

To install this plugin:

1. Copy the folder lj-widget/lj-widget into wp-content/plugins

2. Activate it in your wp-admin page under Plugins.

3. Put it somewhere in your wp-admin page under Appearance > Widgets. You will
   be prompted for a LiveJournal user or community name.
